Residents of Mlolongo and Syokimau estates, Machakos county, have urged the government to build footbridges across Mombasa Road to end accidents.They said cases of pedestrians being run over by speeding vehicles at two different zebra crossings located at the Syokimau stage and Olympic filling station in Mlolongo town are at alarming levels.&ldquo;We are concerned as residents by the increased numbers of people dying on the zebra crossings. A man was run over by a speeding vehicle three days after the zebra crossing at Olympic filling station was done,&rdquo; Activities Action and Answers, a CBO, organising secretary Daniel Mwanza said yesterday.